issues.suggested_fix:
Remove the required 'limit' request parameter from the server GET /persons endpoint (or make it optional with a default). The endpoint should accept only the sorting query parameters (sortField and sortingOrder) with the defaults ID and ASCENDING as described in the problem. For example, change the method signature to

public ResponseEntity<List<Person>> getAllPersons(
    @RequestParam(value = "sortField", defaultValue = "ID") PersonSortingOptions.SortField sortField,
    @RequestParam(value = "sortingOrder", defaultValue = "ASCENDING") PersonSortingOptions.SortingOrder sortingOrder) {
    List<Person> allPersons = personService.getAllPersons(new PersonSortingOptions(sortingOrder, sortField));
    return ResponseEntity.ok(allPersons);
}

Alternatively, if a limit is desired, update the problem statement and the client to document and send the 'limit' parameter (and make it optional on the server with a reasonable default) so all artifacts stay consistent.
